        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 5:13PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 513 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Brighton, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Troy, Southfield, Pontiac, Novi, Brighton, Milford, Royal Oak,
Hamburg, Birmingham, Rochester, South Lyon, Detroit Zoo, West
Bloomfield, Whitmore Lake, Farmington Hills, Rochester Hills, Madison
Heights, Oak Park, Auburn Hills, and Ferndale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
